Description: Scans photos, negatives & slides to DVD.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: GoPhoto provides a professional scanning service to convert old photos, slides, and negatives into digital format on DVD. Includes free online albums where users can edit, tag and share photos with friends and family via Facebook, Twitter and Email in just one click. GoPhoto also converts VHS tapes to DVD.Customers can estimate their order at www.GoPhoto.com by entering approximately how many images they have to scan. Scans of photos, slides and negatives, color or black-and-white, are just $0.28 each. GoPhoto accepts any organization of images, including slide carousels, envelopes of loose photos or even photo albums, all at no additional fee. Customers can then print a pre-paid UPS label to affix to their box for shipping to GoPhoto. No payment is due until photos are scanned and available for viewing online. Packages are tracked via UPS door-to-door from the customer's house to GoPhoto's California-based scanning facility. In addition, the customer receives email notifications throughout the scanning process: once the box is shipped, received, processed, completed and returned. At GoPhoto's scanning facility, one digital imaging expert is assigned to an order from start to finish.  After scanning, each image is individually reviewed and cropped, oriented and color-corrected as needed. GoPhoto also removes dust, minor scratches, and fixes red eyes. Photos are hand-scanned at 600 dpi resolution using professional Epson and Nikon scanners. Any photo scan, sizes up to 8x10, color or black-and-white, costs $0.28 each. Slides and negatives are scanned at 3,000 dpi resolution and are also $0.28 each (per image, not strip). Special Media options such as APS format film or medium format negatives are available at an extra cost. Processing usually takes 10-14 business days; 5-day rush service is available at a 30% service charge.   Once the images are scanned, the customer is notified via email that they can view their images online. Customers have the option to delete any images they don't want, and pay only for those they keep. Once they pay, customers receive their images back, via UPS, along with a DVD of the digital scans. Additional DVDs copies are available at $4.95 each. Customers have the option to edit, title and share their images in their free online albums at GoPhoto.com. Individual images or entire albums can be shared via Facebook, Twitter or email in just one click. Customers can also upload images from other online galleries or a digital camera to GoPhoto's photo gallery to create one comprehensive album of images.GoPhoto can also pre-load the customer's images to a USB Drive for portable storage or a Digital Frame that holds over 6,000 images to create a fun slideshow. GoPhoto also offers gift cards for special occasions.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Information Technology, Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Messaging and Telecommunications

Description: The world's leading provider of smart and hands free chargers for Electric Vehicles (EVs).
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: ConnectMyEV - based in Silicon Valley and formerly known as Green-Dot-Charging, is the world's leading provider of smart and hands free chargers for Electric Vehicles (EVs). ConnectMyEVâs charging system is based on its proprietary conductive hands free charging technology which is 100% efficient and is scalable to high power levels required for DC fast charging. Being conductive, itâs capable of orchestrating large power swings to optimally take advantage of real-time energy pricing. This can significantly lower the cost of charging your EV and in some cases even pay you back to charge.   ConnectMyEV, technology can be retrofitted onto an EV or can be deployed as an add-on accessory at the time of EV purchase. The charging system comprises of (i) a ground side unit, (ii) a vehicle side unit, (iii) a dongle that plugs into OBD-II port, (iv) a wall unit and (v) an app for your smart phone. The ground side unit has a low profile and it can be placed on the surface of garage floor or where you would normally park your EV - such as a driveway. The vehicle side unit - which is the size of a smartphone, receives the energy from the deployed arm of ground side unit. The energy received is routed to the SAE-J-1772 charge port that exists on all EVs.
